--------------------------------------------------------------------
--
--      These source files may be used and distributed without
--      restriction.
--
--------------------------------------------------------------------
--
--      Author  John Hillawi
--      Names   mult_gate.v
--		ref_in
		ref_out
--      Purpose This circuit was created for the purpose of
--              comparing simulation performance at Gate
--              Level. It has been placed in the
--              public domain to act as an ongoing metric
--              for comparing performance.
--
--------------------------------------------------------------------
--	
--	This circuit is a gate level model of a 56 x 56 bit 
--	multiplier matrix. The gate count is approximately 
--	25,000 gates. 
--
--------------------------------------------------------------------
--
--      As a guide to running, a typical script (in this case
--      Pragmatic C Software Cver) would be:
--	
--      cver -f mult_gate.vc
--
--      To directly execute mult_gate.v, type this:
--
--	cver mult_gate.v -y ../libs/lca100kgate +libext+.v
--	
--------------------------------------------------------------------
--
--      The simulation testbench reads pairs of 56 bit floating
--      point numbers from a file (ref_in) and presents them
--      to the multiplier matrix. The output is sampled and compared
--      with reference outputs in the file ref_out. The file supplied is 
--	sufficient to run for 774100 ns.
--
--------------------------------------------------------------------


